`python -m tf2onnx.convert --graphdef "PATH/TO/frozen_inference_graph.pb" --output result.onnx --opset 10 --inputs normalized_input_image_tensor:0 --outputs raw_outputs/box_encodings:0,raw_outputs/class_predictions:0`
And the inference session was created properly.

Thank you for looking into it.

I could n't convert with

The model you uploaded only has one protobuf file (frozen_inference_graph.pb).  Can you upload the fine-tuned saved model you are converting?

Thanks.  I was able to reproduce the error:
`INVALID_GRAPH : This is an invalid model. Error in Node:generic_loop_Loop__94 : Node (Pad__1203) has input size 2 not in range [min=1, max=1]`
Looking into it now.
It looks like there is a bug in converting NonMaxSuppressionV4 for opset 10.  If you use opset 11 it should work.  I'm working on fixing the bug now.
